DEFAULTSORT:Queen's Birthday Honours 1998}}\n[[Category:1998 awards]]\n[[Category:Orders, decorations, and medals of Australia]]\n[[Category:1998 in Australia]]\n", "name_user": "NOLA1982", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eGeneral Division:fix typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1998_Queen%27s_Birthday_Honours_(Australia)"}
{"title_page": "Babak Farzaneh", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=November 2013}}\n\n'''Babak Farzaneh''' (born 1964 in [[Tehran]])\n\nResearcher and scholarly, author and professor of Arabic language and literature.\nAfter his college graduation, Farzaneh continued his university education and achieved BSc of Arabic Language and Literature at Isfahan University. In the middle of his career, in 2004, he achieved Associate Professor and at the apex of his educational profession in 2009, he achieved Full Professor. Dr. Farzaneh was invited to University of Toronto as a Visiting Research Associate in January 2011. He fulfilled his researches in the field of Quranic Lexicography at Toronto. Dr. Farzaneh is currently the head of Arabic Language and Literature Department in Islamic Azad University and also the head of Arabic Language and Literature Department in Great Encyclopedia of Islam and Encyclopedia of Iran.\n\n'''Academic Rank''': Professor of Arabic Language and Literature\n\n'''Teaching Experience''': [[Islamic Azad University]], [[Tehran University]] and Visiting Research Associate at Department for Study Of Religion, [[University of Toronto]]\n\n== Published books ==\n# Principles of Translation ( Arabic \u2013 Persian, Persian \u2013 Arabic ), Tehran, Mahboub Publishing Center, February 1998\n# An Introduction to the Basics of Translation, Tehran, Aye Cultural Institute, 2001\n# Recitation and Perception of the Contemporary Arabic Texts, Tehran, Islamic Azad University, 2001\n# Almu\u1e25\u0101dathat Al-Arabiyya Al-Mo'a\u1e63ira, Islamic Azad University, 2003\n# Contents of the Transcripts of the kazan University, Tatarstan Republic, Russia Federation, Document and Diplomatic History Division, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Tehran, Library of Ayatollah Mar'ash\u012b Najaf\u012b and Global Treasury of Islamic Transcriptions- Qom, 2003\n# Translation of a New Arabic Grammar of the Written Language, Author J. A Haywood & H. M. Nahmad with the title Dastour e Novin e Zaban e Arabi, Tehran, kimiya asar,2009\n# Mokht\u0101r\u0101t Min al-nu\u1e63\u016b\u1e63 al-mo'\u0101\u1e63ira wa al- 'irf\u0101niyyat, Tehran, Shokufehaye Danesh Publisher, 2009\n# Mufrada\u0101t of the Qur\u02bc\u0101n (Researches on the History of Arabic & Quranic Lexicons),Tehran, Study and Compilation of Academic Human Sciences Books Center, 2010\n\n== Published articles ==\n\n===In encyclopedias===\n# Istifh\u0101m, Great Islamic Encyclopedia(GIE), Vol. 8, 1998.\n# Ibn Zubayr(Abul\u1e25asan A\u1e25mad b. Ali), Great Islamic Encyclopedia(Arabic), Vol. 3, 1998.\n# Ibn Zubayr(Abu Mu\u1e25ammad \u1e25asan b. Ali), Great Islamic Encyclopedia(Arabic), Vol. 3, 1998.\n# Ishtiq\u0101q, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 9, 2000.\n# Addition(I\u1e0d\u0101fa) in Morphology and Syntax Of Arabic, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 9, 2000.\n# A\u02bfsh\u0101 hamd\u0101n, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 9, 2000.\n# Algh\u0101z va A\u1e25\u0101j\u012b, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 10, 2001.\n# Alfiyyah, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 10. 2001.\n# Bad\u012bya, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 11, 2002.\n# B\u0101r\u016bd\u012b, Ma\u1e25m\u016bd, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 11, 2002.\n# Badal, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 11, 2002.\n# Badi\u02bf, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 11, 2002.\n# Badi\u02bfiyya, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 11, 2002.\n# Bij\u0101na, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 11, 2002\n# Ta\u1e63r\u012bf, Islamic World License, Vol. 7, 2003.\n# Ta\u1e63gh\u012br, Islamic World License, Vol. 7, 2003.\n# Tarkh\u012bm, Islamic World License, Vol. 7, 2003.\n# Tanw\u012bn, Islamic World License, Vol. 8, 2004.\n# Bal\u0101ghat(Rhetoric), Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 12, 2004.\n# Bay\u0101n(Expression), Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 13, 2005.\n# Abd Allah b.Abd al Muttalib, Encyclopaedia Islamica, Volume I, Brill, London 2008.\n# Abd Allah b. Ja\u1e25sh, Encyclopaedia Islamica, Volume I, Brill, London, 2008.\n# Abd Allah b.Musa b.Nusayr, Encyclopaedia Islamica, Volume I, Brill, London, 2008.\n# Abd Man\u0101f, Encyclopaedia Islamica, Volume I, Brill, London, 2008.\n# Tashb\u012bh(Similie), Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 15, 2008.\n# Tar\u1e63\u012b\u02bb, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 15, 2008.\n# Taft\u0101z\u0101ni, Mu\u1e6dawwal, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 15, 2008.\n# Taw\u0101bi\u02bf, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 16, 2008.\n# Tahm\u0101ni b. \u02bfAmr Kil\u0101b\u012b, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol.16, 2008.\n# Th\u0101bit b. Mo\u1e25ammad Jurj\u0101n\u012b, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 17, 2009.\n# Tham\u0101n\u012bn\u012b, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol.17, 2009.\n# J\u0101\u1e25i\u1e93, Al-\u1e24ayw\u0101n, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol.17, 2009.\n# J\u0101mid wa Mushtaq, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol.17, 2009.\n# Jarm\u012b, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol.17, 2009.\n# Ja\u02bffar b. ulbat \u1e25\u0101rith\u012b, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol.17, 2009.\n# Jir\u0101n al-\u02bfawd, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol.17, 2009.\n# Study and Teaching of Arabic Language, Encyclopaedia Islamica, London, Undergone Publishing.\n# Jumay\u1e25, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Undergone Publishing.\n# Jand\u012b, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 18. 2010\n# Jaz\u02beir\u012b, Great Islamic Encyclopedia,. Vol. 18. 2010\n# Jumla, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 18. 2010.\n# Jam\u012bl Al-Mudawwar, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 18. 2010.\n# \u1e62\u0101\u1e25ib b. \u02bbAbb\u0101d, Daneshnam e zaban e farsii, Undergone Publishing.\n# \u1e24ass\u0101n b. M\u0101lik, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Undergone Publishing.\n# \u1e24arf Ta\u02bfr\u012bf(Definitive), Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Undergone Publishing.\n# \u1e24armala b. Mun\u1e0fir, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Undergone Publishing.\n\n===In journals===\n# \"A look at the Properties of Arabic Poems before Islam\", Sokhan Ahl-e- Del, Monthly Journal, 1993.\n# \"Madiheh and Chanting\", Sokhan Ahl-e- Del, Monthly Journal, 1993.\n# \"Torkan Era\", Sokhan Ahl-e- Del, Monthly Journal, 1993.\n# \"a brief look at the history of morphology and critique knowledge and an investigation of the Shafieh book by Ibn \u1e24ajib\", Faculty of Literature, Journal of Tehran University, P. 105-114, 2002.\n# \"How to use basic Cultures in Arabic Language\", Theology professional letter, Seasonal Journal, P. 1, No. 1, 2003.\n# \"Translation of the Present Continuous verbs in Quran\", Investigation and Articles of Theology Faculty of Tehran University Journal, P 103-115, 2004.\n# \"Dir\u0101s\u0101tun \u1e25awla \u0121ar\u012bb al-qur\u02bc\u0101n va al \u1e25ad\u012bth\", Scientific and Research Journal Religious Research, No. 12, 2005.\n# \"Meanings of the verb K\u0101da in Quran\", Scientific Research Journal of Sahifeh Mobin, No. 37, 2006.\n# \"Zamakhshar\u012b wa Kashsh\u0101f\", Scientific Research Journal of Sahifeh Mobin, No. 38, 2006.\n# \"Evolution of Arabic Alphabet under the protection of Quran\", Scientific Research letter of Quran and Hadith, Second year, No. 2, 2007.\n# \"Muga\u1e6d\u1e6da\u02bbat Alphabet in Quran and its Secrets in Media\", Scientific Research Journal of sahifeh Mobin, No. 43, 2008.\n# \"Tatimmat al Yat\u012bmat Revised by Abas Eghbal\", M\u012br\u0101th Makt\u016bb Publisher.\n# \"Notes on some Persian words in the works of al-\u011e\u0101\u1e25i\u1e93\", Arabica,58,436-445, Brill, Leiden, 2011.\n# \"Syntactic Eloquence of Passive Structures in the holy Quran\", Scientific Research Journal of sahifeh Mobin, No. 47, 2010.\n# \" The Semantics of \u1e24a\u1e63ab in the Kuran,Notes on the Bellamy's article : \"Some Proposed Emendations to the Text of the Kuran\", Sahifeh Mob\u012bn, No. 49, 2012\n\n== Conferences attended ==\n# \"Religious Violence and Nonviolence\", Religion and Human Phenomenon, World Congress International Association History of Religions, University of Toronto, 15\u201322 August 2010.\n# \"A Comparative Lexical Analysis of the Firewood of hell(Ha\u1e63abu \u011fahannama)\", Free Linguistics Conference, University of Sydney, Australia, sep 6, 2010\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.cgie.org.ir/ \u0645\u0631\u06a9\u0632 \u062f\u0627\u0626\u0631\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0639\u0627\u0631\u0641 \u0628\u0632\u0631\u06af \u0627\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645\u06cc]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110726153853/http://iau-tnb.iau.ofis.ir/default.aspx?general&member=3404 OFIS General Information - Islamic Azad University]\n* [http://www.noormags.com/view/fa/Creator/19550 Noor Magazines]\n* [https://openlibrary.org/authors/OL6823966A/Prof.Babak_Farzaneh Open Library]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Farzaneh, Babak}}\n[[Category:Iranian Arabists]]\n[[Category:Islamic Azad University faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Tehran faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Toronto faculty]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=November 2013}}\n\n'''Babak Farzaneh''' (born 1964 in [[Tehran]])\n\nResearcher and scholarly, author and professor of Arabic language and literature.\nAfter his college graduation, Farzaneh continued his university education and achieved BSc of Arabic Language and Literature at Isfahan University. In the middle of his career, in 2004, he achieved Associate Professor and at the apex of his educational profession in 2009, he achieved Full Professor. Dr. Farzaneh was invited to University of Toronto as a Visiting Research Associate in January 2011. He fulfilled his researches in the field of Quranic Lexicography at Toronto. Dr. Farzaneh is currently the head of Arabic Language and Literature Department in Islamic Azad University and also the head of Arabic Language and Literature Department in Great Encyclopedia of Islam and Encyclopedia of Iran.\n\n'''Academic Rank''': Professor of Arabic Language and Literature\n\n'''Teaching Experience''': [[Islamic Azad University]], [[Tehran University]] and Visiting Research Associate at Department for Study Of Religion, [[University of Toronto]]\n\n== Published books ==\n# Principles of Translation ( Arabic \u2013 Persian, Persian \u2013 Arabic ), Tehran, Mahboub Publishing Center, February 1998\n# An Introduction to the Basics of Translation, Tehran, Aye Cultural Institute, 2001\n# Recitation and Perception of the Contemporary Arabic Texts, Tehran, Islamic Azad University, 2001\n# Almu\u1e25\u0101dathat Al-Arabiyya Al-Mo'a\u1e63ira, Islamic Azad University, 2003\n# Contents of the Transcripts of the kazan University, Tatarstan Republic, Russia Federation, Document and Diplomatic History Division, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Tehran, Library of Ayatollah Mar'ash\u012b Najaf\u012b and Global Treasury of Islamic Transcriptions- Qom, 2003\n# Translation of a New Arabic Grammar of the Written Language, Author J. A Haywood & H. M. Nahmad with the title Dastour e Novin e Zaban e Arabi, Tehran, kimiya asar,2009\n# Mokht\u0101r\u0101t Min al-nu\u1e63\u016b\u1e63 al-mo'\u0101\u1e63ira wa al- 'irf\u0101niyyat, Tehran, Shokufehaye Danesh Publisher, 2009\n# Mufrada\u0101t of the Qur\u02bc\u0101n (Researches on the History of Arabic & Quranic Lexicons),Tehran, Study and Compilation of Academic Human Sciences Books Center, 2010\n\n== Published articles ==\n\n===In encyclopedias===\n# Istifh\u0101m, Great Islamic Encyclopedia(GIE), Vol. 8, 1998.\n# Ibn Zubayr(Abul\u1e25asan A\u1e25mad b. Ali), Great Islamic Encyclopedia(Arabic), Vol. 3, 1998.\n# Ibn Zubayr(Abu Mu\u1e25ammad \u1e25asan b. Ali), Great Islamic Encyclopedia(Arabic), Vol. 3, 1998.\n# Ishtiq\u0101q, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 9, 2000.\n# Addition(I\u1e0d\u0101fa) in Morphology and Syntax Of Arabic, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 9, 2000.\n# A\u02bfsh\u0101 hamd\u0101n, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 9, 2000.\n# Algh\u0101z va A\u1e25\u0101j\u012b, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 10, 2001.\n# Alfiyyah, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 10. 2001.\n# Bad\u012bya, Great Islamic Encyclopedia, Vol. 11, 2002.\n# B\u0101r\u016bd\u012b, Ma\u1e25m\u016bd, Great Islamic